In Qatar, the CDP is responsible for the enforcement of the Data Protection Law. Any data subject may submit a complaint to the CDP in the case of a violation of the Data Protection Law. The CDP will investigate the complaint and, if the complaint is found to be valid, the CDP can oblige the data controller or processor to rectify the violation within a specified time period.
The CDP can also impose fines of up to&nbsp;5 million (US$1.4 million) for violations of the Data Protection Law.Last modified 17 Jan 2022
				
			